tags: i’m sorry to burst your bubble
body:
Spider-Man’s Birthday

Attention everyone attention please. If I could just take a moment of your time. So, apparently people have been going around saying it’s Peter’s birthday but I’m afraid that I will have to burst your bubble because today is NOT Peter’s birthday. Actually today is the ANNIVERSARY of Spider-Man’s debut into the comic world. Peter’s actual birthday according to the Amazing Spider-Man comic #700, it’s October 18th. So, Happy Anniversary Spider-Man!

summary:
This is how that relationship ends
Ironman befriends and mentors Spider-Man during the original Civil War (just like in the...
body:
Dear fans of the creepy Ironman X Spider-Man sub fandom

This is how that relationship ends

Ironman befriends and mentors Spider-Man during the original Civil War (just like in the movies)

Ironman “hypes” Spidey’s career, makes him the Iron Spider suit (just like in the movies)

Ironman encourages Spider-Man to go public with his identity, against Peter’s better judgement- which later gets Aunt May killed which then ruins his marriage with MJ

Spider-Man has a change of heart and conscience and decides to leave Iron-Man’s side of the civil war after seeing the implications of his agenda

Which then leads to Ironman beating the shit outta Spidey. And that suit he made Peter? Now Tony knows everything there is to know about Spider-Man’s power set and abilities and USES IT AGAINST HIM in a way that’s definitely a betrayal of intimacy, trust and vulnerability.

So please, I beg y’all, stop writing creepy pseudo-romantic fanfiction of these two. If not for the implied pedophilic undertones, then do it so you don’t feel crushed when the reality of Tony’s dysfunctional relationships (plural) become too apparent to ignore. I’m not saying Tony is evil or sets out with bad intentions, he isn’t and he doesn’t. But dude is mentally and emotionally unstable from childhood issues, which is fair, legit and relatable, and I really wish we’d stop pretending he doesn’t need serious help.

And no, a relationship with a child is not the help he needs. And you know that.
